it of $9.6 billion and now it''s down to less than half that. Now the company is breaking down the reasons behind the drop, and everything starts with the flagship Galaxy S smartphones. Reuters notes that phones drove its growth over the last couple of years, but profits in that area dropped from 6.7 trillion Korean won last year, to 1.75 trillion in the same period this year. That drop came as a result of price cuts for older phones and "declined shipments" of high-end models. Even slightly higher sales of midrange smartphones apparently weren''t enough to right the ship, and the Galaxy Note 4 hasn''t been on sale long enough to contribute. Worse, the phone sales have an effect across the company for its display, memory and CPU businesses. It expects to sell more Ultra HD and curved TVs to close out 2014, but investors will likely be more interested in how it responds to cheaper Chinese phone manufacturers. \r  \r   \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Source: Samsung, Q3 2014 Earnings slides (PDF)\r More Coverage: Reuters, Bloomberg, Wall Street Journal\r \r \r \r  Tags: hdpostcross, mobilepostcross, samsung\r \r \r \r \r \r \r  Hide Comments\r 0Comments\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r      \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r    \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Featured Stories\r \r \r \r \r Can a head-worn fitness device work? Recon seems to think so\r 2 hours ago  0\r \r \r \r \r Surface 3 review: Finally, a cheap Surface you''d actually want\r 16 hours ago  0\r \r \r \r \r Alcatel OneTouch Watch review: No beginner''s luck here\r 21 hours ago  0\r \r \r \r \r Mario Kart 8''s super-fast 200cc class almost made me puke\r 22 hours ago  0\r \r \r \r \r Resurrecting ''Guitar Hero'' through live rock and robots\r 1 day ago  0\r \r \r \r \r ''Guitar Hero'' gets born again with a new look and a new controller\r 1 day ago  0\r \r \r \r \r Sony''s new compact cameras put a superzoom lens in your pocket\r 2 days ago  0\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r  Sponsored Content\