(150, 'Search for a Company by Name Home | Awards | Comparisons | Index | FAQ | Blog Samsung Customer Service User Reviews, Ratings and Comments Samsung customer service is ranked #484 out of the 796 companies that have a CustomerServiceScoreboard.com rating with an overall score of 29.65 out of a possible 200 based upon 2165 ratings. This score rates Samsung customer service and customer support as Terrible. NEGATIVE Comments 2,060 Negative Comments out of 2,165 Total Comments is 95.15%. POSITIVE Comments 105 Positive Comments out of 2,165 Total Comments is 4.85%. Issue Resolution Reachability Cancellation Friendliness Product Knowledge Negative Comments (2,060) Positive Comments (105) Employee Comments (4) Submit your comment >> Viewing Samsung customer service complaints 1 - 25 out of 2,060 Next >> I have taken my samsung core 2 into the service centre in Phuket town for the 3rd time with the same problem. The last time it was in for 1 week. I called to find out when it''ll be ready. I was told that it would be 2-3 days as they were waiting for a part to come from Bangkok. That same day about 2 hours later, I got a text message saying it was ready for collection. I want to take this matter further. Anonymous 4/16/15 4:10AM My 4 months old Samsung 4 is already at repairs. I don''t recall dropping in however this morning I find a slight crack on the inside. My phone wouldn''t work not even to back up. I took photos because there is not a single scratch on the outside. Unbelievable my previous mobile (an HTC) was dropped a 5m height, screen broke but I continued using it for 14 months. I don''t recall dropping my samsung, a get a crack out of nowhere, and my mobile is out. To make things worse, this is not covered by insurance and I have to pay ?165 for the repairs. Wow I thought I''m going to upscale with samsung but HTC is more durable. Joanne 4/16/15 3:41AM Interesting enough I have been posting my problem on samsung facebook pages and getting a lot of very similar mocking comments. The strange thing is that it started out of nowhere and people usually do not take their time to mock other people''s concerns! How something like that happens in Canada and there is no accountability or the minimum of respect from big corporations like sumsung at all when it comes to consumer rights????!!!!!!! All you get for complaining with sumsung facebook pages is mocking!!!!!! Daniela Tereshchuk 4/15/15 4:39PM The People Working At Samsung Support Are Idiots. They Can Not Get Anything Done To Save Their Lives. I Was Transferred 5 Times To Morons And My Issue Still Isnt Resolved. All I Need Is A Warrenty Swap On A Defective Accessory. They Suck!! Mike 4/15/15 3:00PM I paid $1100 for a Samsung model TV a little over 4 years ago. It just quit working about a week ago. I called to file a claim and they basically wouldn''t let me. They actually had the nerve to try and sell me an extended service plan on my dead TV. The worst part about it was that the 1st 2 people I spoke with, who were selling the plan quite hard, couldn''t even tell me how much it would be. They also had no explanation as to why they were not standing behind their product. When i was transferred to the service warranty department, they quoted over $350 which only included parts and labor for repairs. In the event that they couldn''t fix it they offered to refund the $350 but would not replace the TV or refund the purchase price. When I pointed out that I could purchase a new TV for $350 that would actually last more that 4 years they didn''t seem to care. My advise to anyone is steer clear of all Samsung products and their reprehensible "Customer Service". I only wish i did a little more research about the company before I threw my money away on there poor quality "Products". Don''t make the same mistake i did, it will cost you. FJ from NJ 4/15/15 1:18PM Glasstop defect of Samsung range Model number I am outraged as I have been accused by Samsung for something that I did not do, and Samsung refused to repair a problem caused by its manufacturing defects. We bought the Samsung electric range from a hhgregg Store in Virginia Beach, and have used it for less than 8 months before the glass top of one heating unit cracked on its own. This happened when cooking was already done for at least 30 minutes, as we have finished eating and cleaning. While I was reading my iPad, I heard a loud noise, but didnâ??t pay too much attention. When it was time to cook again, I noticed the crack. Over the next 24 hours, the crack further extended. Since itâ??s still under the 1 year manufacturerâ??s warranty, I called Samsung. Samsung made an appointment for me and said a technician would come to my home to investigate. I received a phone call the next day from Virginia Electronics, a 3rd party repairer contracted with Samsung. I was asked to take some pictures of the cracks and email the pictures to ''[email protected]''. Since the cracks in the dark glass were not easy to see in the pictures, in one picture I used a white marker of the paint tool to outline the cracks in one of the photos. Four days went by. I received a phone call while at work. It was from the third party repairer, and I was told t that the technical team at Samsung had determined the cracks were caused by â??physical damageâ??, therefore it is not covered by Samsungâ??s warranty. I was then quoted $467 for a repair, which is almost the price of a new range. I was mad to hear what I was told, as neither me nor my wife had ever dropped anything heavy onto the surface. Itâ??s the first range that we have owned, and we treated it like a baby. Of course I refused to believe that it was a physical damage. So, I called Samsung. During my 1.5 hours conversation on the phone with customer service ladies of various levels, I was repeatedly given the same message: all these ladies could see from their computers were the pictures that I sent to them, and the two words underneath the pictures -physical damage; there was nothing that they could do, since it has already been â??determinedâ?? a â??physical damageâ?? by the trained technical team. I was once transferred by a supervisor with the first name Jessica back to the 3rd party repair center when I asked to talk to Samsungâ??s technical engineers, throwing me back to the circle of getting nowhere. She was also the one who told me that she could ask technicians to come to my house to investigate, but the result would be the same, as the decision was already made, and that all they could do if they come was to take pictures and bring the pictures back to the same reviewing team, and I would have to pay for their travel. One of the representatives (Latoya) took a short break chatting with another person in the background and laughed out of context as if she was enjoying listening to my trembling voice of anger. The last supervisor (Beth, agent code 83578) explained to me how job is done at her support center: 1) the customer sends photos to the 3rd party; 2) this third party contacts Samsungâ??s repair center via some internet portal to forward the photos; 3) this behind-the-scene â??trained expertsâ?? make a decision based off the pictures whether the fault is at the customer or due to manufacturing defect; 4) that decision is send back to the 3rd party repair center and Samsungâ??s customer support. Beth also explained that â??physical damagesâ?? can be caused by improper cleaning leading to scratches, or dropping heavy objects onto the surface any time before the crack happens. According to her, while I did not drop anything heavy onto my range, since these experts have studied the pictures and decided that it was my fault, so all she could say was sorry. I found this ridiculous, not only because Samsung has refused to take its responsibility, but more importantly it was insulting the customer for something that he did not do!! Where is justice!!!? I was given two email addresses after I pressed them really hard. The complaint department is s the product support team that determines whether the problem is a defect or physical damage is . I seriously doubt that either will get me out of the hopeless loop, if theyâ??ll ever respond. But I will update if Samsung makes any sensible action. Dr. 4/15/15 12:56PM I am a busy mom who has taken the time to write here so other consumers do not go through the frustrating experience I am going through with Samsung....and I am not alone!!!! a lot of other Canadians have shared their views on Samsung consumer services practices in Canada....in my opinion, I feel like there is such a push from the big retailers that everybody buys extended warranty( I had a stamp on my receipt saying I had refused to buy extended warranty at Staples) so stores can make more money and manufacturers can get away with poor quality products and no consideration to consumers...There is no accountability! it is a very concerning where we are heading in terms of consumers rights! I bought a defaulted printer 3 months ago, and sumsung has been relying in sneaky fine prints and after going back back and forth for hours on the phone, now they dont even bother to answer my email and nothing got resolved...I bought a defaulted printer and as far as I am concerned Samsung do not stand by the quality of their products and do not care about their consumers, just ignoring their problems...basically if you buy a defaulted product...it''s all the consumer''s loss!!!!! Daniela Tereshchuk 4/14/15 4:48PM My first time and I have to say Samsung customer service is as bad as I heard it was. 2013 Evolution Kit was defective (broke WiFi and networking settings capability). Trying to get it replaced was a nightmare of incompetence, misunderstandings and convoluted processes. So bad in fact that I will take much more interest in other brands for my next purchase. Anonymous 4/13/15 4:17PM I emailed this message to Samsung and was told it would permanently be disregarded. The new update has a few problems .I can''t use or read emoji on my st8 games. I could see, use and read more emoji before the update. I also can''t edit a picture before I post on palringo. I used this feature often before the update. Now I have to edit the photo before I can post it on palringo which is an extra step. The emoji issue is most annoying since all iPhone users and most android users use it as additional language in online games by storm8. All I get is a blank space. And it is necessary to read clan names on these games too otherwise everyone has a blank space and looks like they are not working to play the game within a clan structure. The third thing that is irritating is the little tiny circle picture on my phone contacts. I have a note 4 and i need a magnifying glass to see the picture. That was very readable before the update. I think I''d like to go back to the old version if these issues can''t be fixed soon like within a month at most. If this is not feasible send me directions to go back to my old version prior to the update. I don''t have 5g capacity in my location anyway. Thank you for your time and concern. I''d appreciate an answer to this text asap. Sharon Allan PS I was very happy with my note 4 and I switched from Motorola to Samsung. I hope to be glad I changed companies once again. sharon allan 4/13/15 2:00PM So #samsung is really playing with us... First we bought a brand new laser printer for a sale price of $189.00 after researching for the best printers, we were so exited it arrived the next day, until I turned it on and it sounded like a gears crashing together, I couldn''t print, and within seconds a red light comes up saying error code, blah blah. We contacted the company we bought with but next thing we no they want us to return and cancel the order so we can buy another from them even though the sale price ended and was now $289.00 still on sale but still also $100 more then I was originally paying! We decided to go to the company head of Samsung and were told sorry. Promised for a fixed printer and sent it back. When it arrived 1 week later again I was excited to start, this is my business and I NEED this printer which I express to Samsung. They sent printed out sheets saying this is what they got out of my printer, and then proceeded to tell me that is had nothing wrong! Turn it on, and within second my 3 month old wakes up screaming cause the printer is grinding so loud! Bull crap nothing is wrong. Did you even turn it on!? Now we have been playing phone games with them, we were promised a phone call within 24 hours from the higher up for a brand new one, no more of this running around crap, it has now been 48 hours with us calling 3 times each promise we will be called back in 2 hours, then NOTHING! I tried being patient, I tried working with you as businesses and customers should do, however I don''t get how you could have such a blunt disrespect for your customers. Your company didn''t get anywhere without them, so buck up and fix this! Or I will continue to stock, harass and attack your Facebook and social medias until I get what I was bloody promised! Hilliary dunford 4/10/15 6:30AM Phonecall 6 Minutes (0,60 ? each) for zero information. I stated: "I bought a Samsung S3 in China, and now back in Europe I tried to load apps in Googleplay store (but it said "no Device found"); what can I do?" The Samsung professional answered: "You bought your mobile in China. You cannot download Googleplay store." Thank you Samsung, perfect Apple promotion CN_customer 4/10/15 2:28AM Samsung product are reasonably good because of China Engineers , else therr Indian Service Team is non business & non customer care. They are just wasting customrmer time & money when they know issue. even there seniors donot bother , if you get service or product. its by technology samsung is running , no effort by india team , other than counting money. Sango 4/9/15 8:14PM I believe in spending more money and buying quality SAMSUNG stuff but i was wrong, its been very disappointing that the products i bought needs repair withing 1week or 6 Months. Following items:- LED 42" TV 2009- Screen flickering, replaced with new TV BUT AFTER 1 YEAR same problem with that too, luckily i have extended warranty and they fixed it. Samsung Galaxy TAB3 2013:- Power Failure after 1 year, Repaired Samsung Mobile galaxy S3 2013- Front Camera stopped working within first 6 months Samsung Laptop 2010 Harvey Norman- Motherboard crashed within 1 week of Purchase, Repaired but now its totally gone. Samsung Microwave-Good Guys 06/09/2013-ME6124ST- Faulty, STOPPED WORKING Samsung Washing- No Issues at the moment LG fridge 210L 2010 Model:- No issues till now Please consider this as a serious complaint and as far as i am concerned it will affect your brand name because i won''t be buying any Samsung product in future and have decided not to recommend it to any friend or relatives. SunnyAus 4/8/15 5:14PM Hi, With severe disappointment related to the service provided and with gross indifference to the multiple requests and emails i have written to you i would like to inform you that the issue i have reported with request id 8463956491 has neither resolved nor addressed. It would take very minimal effort for me to take this issue to social media or it to the consumer court, before that i would like to try one last time to get the issue resolved from SAMSUNG itself. Samsung being a premier brand in india with many hardware products in the market should be responsible for its products and violating people''s trust this way would only backfires and there would be no time SAMSUNG would be butt of people jokes and no one would go for the product. I am attaching here all the documents i have, related to my earlier requests and issues reported for the malafide hardware product i was given. I am hoping this would be last time i need to write to SAMSUNG or else the fight would go on through legal courts and also onto soc