(176, 'Samsung.com website not working? Is it down right now? Samsung.com Server Status Check SamsungWebsite Name: www.samsung.comURL Checked: Response Time: Last Down: Checking Samsung Please wait while we check the server... JavaScript is required. Please enable JavaScript in your browser. Samsung Website Status HistoryThe above graph displays service status activity for Samsung.com over the last 10 automatic checks. The blue bar displays the response time, which is better when smaller. If no bar is displayed for a specific time it means that the service was down and the site was offline. Service Status History DateTimePing Time DateTimePing Time15.Apr.2015 12:298.72 ms. 15.Apr.2015 15:0125.22 ms.15.Apr.2015 17:041.86 ms. 15.Apr.2015 19:11141.18 ms.15.Apr.2015 21:2125.16 ms. 16.Apr.2015 00:0823.7 ms.16.Apr.2015 02:4423.49 ms. 16.Apr.2015 05:161.13 ms.16.Apr.2015 07:551.42 ms. 16.Apr.2015 10:021.32 ms.  * Times displayed are PT, Pacific Time (UTC/GMT 0)  |  Current server time is 12:25We have tried pinging Samsung website using our server and the website returned the above results. If samsung.com is down for us too there is nothing you can do except waiting. Probably the server is overloaded, down or unreachable because of a network problem, outage or a website maintenance is in progress... Can''t Access Samsung - Troubleshooting Instructions If the site is UP but you cant access the page, try one of the below solutions: Browser Related Problems Force a full refresh for the site. This can be achieved by pressing CTRL + F5 keys at the same time on your favourite browser (Firefox, Chrome, Explorer, etc.)Clear the temporary cache and cookies on your browser to make sure that you have the most recent version of the web page. For instructions choose your browser : Fix DNS Problems A Domain Name System (DNS) allows a site IP address (192.168.x.x) to be identified with words (*.com) in order to be remembered more easily, like a phonebook for websites. This service is usually provided by your ISP. Clear your local DNS cache to make sure that you grab the most recent cache that your ISP has. For Windows - (Start > Command Prompt > type "ipconfig /flushdns" and hit enter). For details choose your operating system : If you can access a website at office or from a 3G network yet it''s not working on your computer, it is a good idea to use an alternative DNS service other than your ISPs. OpenDNS or Google Public DNS are both excellent and free public DNS services. Check our help page for step-by-step instructions on how to change your DNS. Having Problems with Accessing Samsung.com? ? LAST 12 HOURS ... Bob Vidoni · 1 hour 20 mins ago 0 · · Safari 8.0.5 on Mac 55" Samsung 4k HDTV-All apps disappeared. Only option to download appears. Click on download now....message appears: This action not supported....this happens for all apps...at least a week now...all other internet sources work.....all settings confirmed....this is a google server for Samsung...Smart Hub one of the main reasons we bought this newer Samsung TV to replace an older 50" Samsung HDTV...disappointing ? YESTERDAY ... Colleen Whitelaw-Syrett · 1 day 15 hours ago 0 · · Android Browser 4.0 on Android Samsung smart tv wont connect to internet. Is the samsung network really down again? Jude Mulhuijsen · 1 day 20 hours ago 0 · · Firefox 37.0 on Windows Samsung hub not working in Kenya either... I''ve only tried You Tube in the past few days but it just shows a black page, nothing happens, I don''t even see the You Tube logo... anybody know how to fix this?! Gary Webb · 1 day 23 hours ago 0 · · Chrome 41.0 on Windows Save yourself a lot of aggravation...get a Roku ? LAST 7 DAYS ... Jennifer Gordon · 4 days 12 hours ago 0 · · Safari 8.0 on iPad Network interference on Samsung Smart TV. It''s not us it''s them. Everything else I own works fine except smart hub. I can get into Netflix by clicking on the advertisement on smart hub. I''ve tried all the list fixes I could find nothing works. It''s been down for at least 3 days! Christy Schaller · 10 April 2015 - 01:12 1 · · Safari 8.0 on iPad Stopped working at 2100hrs EST... Anyone know the reason? ? LAST 30 DAYS ... Diana Cardona · 9 April 2015 - 05:18 0 · · Safari 8.0 on iPad Samsung smart hub is not working for at least two days. Los Angeles, CA. Bryan Sledge · 8 April 2015 - 23:57 0 · · Chrome 41.0 on Android Smarthub is not connecting to any Web-based apps. This has been for at least 3 days. Chicago, IL. Tracy Goggin · 8 April 2015 - 22:51 0 · · Chrome 41.0 on Windows Samsung Smart Hub isn''t connecting to the Internet and I have internet with all other devices in my house. Kevin Mahoney · 7 April 2015 - 16:22 0 · · Internet Explorer 11.0 on Windows I have changed DNS to google DNS 8.8.8.8 and 8.8.4.4 still nothing Leo Valaris · 3 April 2015 - 05:42 1 · · Safari 600.1.4 on iPad Samsung Smart Hub is reporting that it cannot connect to the Internet. Internet is up, just can''t connect to it from Samsung TV - April 3 2015. Nick Evans · 3 April 2015 - 05:06 0 · · Safari 8.0 on iPad I''m having the same issue. samsung may be down again. Its behaving the same as during the outage in February. Mistie Taylor · 3 April 2015 - 03:50 1 · · Safari 7.0 on iPhone Same problem as in feb!! Keeps saying network interference try again later!!! I go into network settings says network setting complete but cannot connect to internet contact service provider!!! I called samsung they said change dns settings to 8, 8, 8, 8 it worked but now I can''t watch my American Netflix (I''m in canada) but I even tried putting it back to auto and resetting to to original settings it DOES NOT work only works to the 8, 8, 8, 8!!! So I''m hoping/assuming it''s the Samsung server ? MORE THAN 6 MONTHS AGO ... Alexander Christiaan Principaal · 27 May 2014 - 02:51 3 Netherlands · Unet · Firefox 29.0 on Windows Eroor_bind_model since yesterday reinstalled smarthub with reset as samsung says.Its connected to my pc no problem i can acc