y text and call off (think that was \r my fault mind) but as you can imagine this is worlds apart. If you want an alternative \r to the iPhone look now further. \r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by technostein from UK on 5th Feb 2012\r Had this phone for a couple of Weeks, very pleased with it, much better than \r my HTC sensation speed and design wise. I have.good.knowledge of Android and \r touchwiz user interface is one of the most simplest you can get on android phone. \r Battery life is terrible so got the official\r Samsung extended battery adding only 1mm in thickness. Now this is a perfect \r phone for everything. Strongly recommend.\r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by Gill from England on 4th Feb 2012\r sorry to say very disappointed. Had phone for only a day and was unable to send \r messages apart from brief interval of maybe 30 mins then all failing again. \r Advised by O2 takes 24 hrs to set up everything, but switch on and off every \r hour and if no luck register call with helpdesk!!?? I think not O2 it will be \r back with you shortly. I see on various forums this common p-roblem and not \r exclusive to the initial 24 hrs after purchase. Plus 2 phone calls that were \r totally incomprehensible, also highlighted on forums. On balance my sister has \r had same phone for sometime and it''s been faultless. Everything else on the \r phone fab but if can''t make calls or text when required it''s not up to job!\r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by Scott from uk on 4th Feb 2012\r Like previous reviews I wasn''t sure wether to get another I phone after having \r the 3gs for two years a few of my friends have the 4s but it want different \r enough to warrant a change.had a play with this phone and oh my God this phone \r its amazing, if you are in the same position as I was wondering to get get one \r or not don''t worry you will not be disappointed.my friends who have the 4s wish \r they had got one too !!!\r \r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by Trevor B from UK on 4th Feb 2012\r