r battery for the \r S2 & its called a Extended battery & is 2000mah which now lasts up to 2 days \r ! but you lose the slimness part of the phone & you get the same backcover as \r before but it lines up with the hump at the bottom of the phone which is no \r big deal to me only 1mm difference. Also get a pouch case because those nearly \r fit cases causes the phone to give a echo to the caller when you speak very \r strange, but apart from that its a superb phone get one now they are much cheaper \r on contract than the iphone & has around the same spec as the iphone... I picked \r one up for ?25 per month from Tesco great deal.\r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by Kasser from England on 3rd Feb 2012\r You''ll love this phone, until you want to connect to wifi. It will work for \r a few weeks then BOOM! Nothing! It will show full bars for wifi but there will \r be zero data transferred. Don''t believe me? Google ''wifi Galaxy S2'' and you''ll \r see. This POS is going on ebay and going back to BlackBerry. (Ps, call volume \r is absolute nrubbish as well. Believe it or not, if you lower media volume in, \r say, a game, it affects the volume in a call!!! KOREAN RUBBISH! And don''t even \r get me started on Kies desktop software!!!). GARBAGE.\r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by sarah from wales on 3rd Feb 2012\r Love the phone so glad I got it\r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by Dan from UK on 2nd Feb 2012\r I do like this phone, but it feels a bit plasticy. Its like a wizard purple \r phone!\r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by Kev from UK on 1st Feb 2012\r Best phone out there by far, only gripe is the oral speaker phone is at the \r back and like the numpty i am i keep covering it up with my hand so the caller \r can''t hear me or turning my head away from the phone which has the same effect......get \r one\r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by chris H from uk on 30th Jan 2012\r I pondered for a long time whether to go for the S2 or the 4S (previously was \r a iphone 3GS user). It partily came down to price, S2 contract significantly \r cheaper, and I was really not sure about android having used apple for 2 years. \r All I can say is WOW, the S2 is amazing, I was affaid I wouldn''t get on with \r it, apple is designed for your nan to use it, but I shouldn''t have worried. \r within two days it was ''apple'' who? the screen is amazing, it is super fast, \r has flash, add a memory. I really can''t rate it enough. If like me, you like \r the new tech, but it slightly scares you, especially when you read that you \r can customise etc, fear not, it really isn''t difficult. Video play back is great, \r the camera is amazing, more or less done away with my digital camera and recording \r HD video is brilliant. There are a couple of points to note, as has previosuly \r been mentioned, the app store isn''t as great, IMO, than apple, a lot of second \r rate apps, but there is something out there fore everyone. Also, the battery \r doesn''t last for ages. Most days it will get me through until I go to bed, I''d \r say I am medium user, listen to music, check emails, texting, a few calls, a \r game or two. However, just buy a spare charger, or use one from all other devices \r except apple. If you are wondering which one to go for S2 or 4S, go for the \r S2. And to be fair, I can imagine Siri will get boring after a short time.\r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by gee from uk on 30th Jan 2012\r Xcelent fne had it for two months cnt go rong touch wood\r Rating: \r \r \r Reviewed by GeeBee from Scotland on 29th Jan 2012\r i''ve had this phone for around 4 months. absolutely love it, apart from the \r battery on my phone only lasts almost a day but thats because i always have \r apps running and always texting or calling people. so easy to use. got nothing \r bad to say about the phone at all. i love it!\r Rating: \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r