he Samsung Group can accept or receive service of process on behalf of another. No company within the Samsung Group is legally liable for another unless specifically agreed to in writing to assume such liabilities. This site does not establish any nexus between any of the companies such that you can assume that they can be sued jointly or severally on behalf of another.\r \r   This privacy policy was last updated on July 11, 2005.\r  \r  \r  \r   \r  \r \r \r \r  \r  \r   \r   \r    Business Info\r    Business History\r    Core Technology\r    Global Networks\r   \r  \r \r  \r   \r   \r     Network ProductsAnalog ProductsMonitorsAccessoriesControllersAccess control & SensorsSmart Home Security\r   \r  \r \r  \r   \r   \r    \r    City\r    Military\r    Building\r    Airport\r    Port\r    Utility\r    \r   \r  \r \r  \r   \r   \r    Download Center\r    Technical Info\r    Product Demo\r    Sales & Service\r    Contact Us\r   \r  \r \r  \r   \r   \r    News & Notice\r    \r    Benchmark Report');
INSERT INTO `site_content` (`id`, `content`) VALUES
(164, 'Home\r LCD/LED TV Reviews\r Ratings\r Buying Tips\r Top 10 LCD/LED TVS\r Where to Buy\r Plasma TV Reviews\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Tweet\r \r \r Samsung LCD/LED TV, 4K UHD TV, OLED TV Models and Reviews 2015\r \r By Jack Burden, Robert Wiley, and Phil Conner\r \r \r = Highest Price and Most Features\r \r What is This?This guide reflects the price and feature set within this manufacturer''s TV offerings. It does not include other manufacturer''s TV offerings nor is it a rating from us. Five full circles reflects this manufacturer''s highest price and feature set TV series. One full circle and four empty circles indicates the TV series offered by this manufacturer with the lowest price and least feature set. For further information see our editors choice awards and our TV reviews ratings chart.\r \r \r Samsung 75"+ TV |\r Samsung 65" TV | \r Samsung 60" TV | \r Samsung 55" TV | \r Samsung 50" TV | \r Samsung 46-48" TV | \r Samsung 40" TV | \r Samsung 32" TV | \r Samsung 28" TV | \r Samsung 22" TV | \r Samsung 19" TV\r \r \r Samsung Picture Settings\r \r Click on any of the Samsung TV individual model numbers below to see the full review, pricing, and availability.\r \r \r \r \r \r \r UN65H8000Review\r \r UN55H7150Review\r \r UN55H6350Review\r \r UN50H6400Review\r \r UN48H5500Review\r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung JS9000 Series 4K SUHD LED TV  \r \r The JS9000 is Samsung''s top of the line 4K LED this year. Powerful LED lighting, UHD dimming, and the Nano crystal layer for beautiful color are just some of Samsung best picture quality upgrades you''ll find on this one.\r Samsung UN65JS9000, \r Samsung UN55JS9000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung JS8500 Series 4K SUHD LED TV  \r \r The JS8500 is just a few steps down from the top of the line 4K LED this year. just a few steps down from the top of the line 4K LED this year. The LED backlighting configuration is edge-lit, the web cam is gone, and the Clear Motion Rate has been slightly lowered compared to the JS9000 series.\r Samsung UN65JS8500, \r Samsung UN55JS8500\r \r \r \r \r Samsung JU7500 Curved 4K LED TV  \r \r The JU7500 is nearl the top of the line 4K LED TV in Samsung''s lineup for 2015. Feautures include UHD Picture Dimming, a quad core processor, contrast enhancer technology, precision black and peak illuminator picture quality adjustments. Also, the much upgraded Smart remote with touchpad and mic.\r Samsung UN78JU7500, \r Samsung UN65JU7500, \r Samsung UN55JU7500, \r Samsung UN48JU7500, \r Samsung UN40JU7500\r \r \r \r \r Samsung JU6700 Curved 4K LED TV  \r \r The JU6700 is the entry-level 4K LED TV in Samsung''s lineup for 2015 for those looking for a curve in their screen. They come at a value price, just like the JU6500 below, and offer similar features like Smart TV, UHD Picture Dimming, a quad core processor, HEVC 4K streaming decoding, and a contrast enhancer.\r Samsung UN65JU6700, \r Samsung UN55JU6700, \r Samsung UN48JU6700, \r Samsung UN40JU6700\r \r \r \r \r Samsung JU6500 Series 4K LED TV  \r \r The JU6500 is the entry-level 4K LED TV in Samsung''s lineup for 2015. They come at a value price while still offering plenty of features like Smart TV, UHD Picture Dimming, a quad core processor, HEVC 4K streaming decoding, and a contrast enhancer.\r Samsung UN75JU6500, \r Samsung UN65JU6500, \r Samsung UN60JU6500, \r Samsung UN55JU6500, \r Samsung UN50JU6500, \r Samsung UN48JU6500, \r Samsung UN40JU6500\r \r \r \r \r Samsung JU6500 Series 4K LED TV  \r \r The JU6500 is the entry-level 4K LED TV in Samsung''s lineup for 2015. just a few steps down from the top of the line 4K LED this year. The LED backlighting configuration is edge-lit, the web cam is gone, and the Clear Motion Rate has been slightly lowered compared to the JS9000 series.\r Samsung UN65JS8500, \r Samsung UN55JS8500\r \r \r \r \r Samsung HU9000 Series LED TV  \r \r The HU9000 is the top of the line Samsung LED without counting the OLEDs this year. It is a curved 4K LED display with all the bells and whistles one could wish for. You get Samsung''s top performing smart TV platform, Active 3D, 4K upscaling, and more.\r Samsung UN78HU9000, \r Samsung UN65HU9000, \r Samsung UN55HU9000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung HU8550 Series LED TV  \r \r The HU8550 is Samsung''s flat 4K LED TV for the year. It has all the bells and whistles of the H8000 below it but is missing all the picture quality extras of the HU9000 above it. This is the best of the best when it comes to flat Samsung picture quality for 2014.\r Samsung UN75HU8550, \r Samsung UN65HU8550, \r Samsung UN55HU8550, \r Samsung UN50HU8550\r \r \r \r \r Samsung H8000 Series LED TV  \r \r The H8000 series occupies the middle ground between a standard flat TV and the curved OLEDs we are seeing released this year. This curved 1080p screen features better local dimming than the H7150 series below it. It has all the Smart TV extras packed in as well.\r Samsung UN65H8000, \r Samsung UN55H8000, \r Samsung UN48H8000, \r \r \r \r \r Samsung H7150 Series LED TV  \r \r The H7150 is the best flat 1080p display Samsung has to offer this year. It''s got a 240Hz refresh rate, 3D playback, the new touch pad remote, and the full Samsung Smart TV platform. Some extras include 3D dual view and split screen multitasking.\r Samsung UN75H7150, \r Samsung UN65H7150, \r Samsung UN60H7150, \r Samsung UN55H7150, \r Samsung UN46H7150, \r \r \r \r \r Samsung H6400 Series LED TV  \r \r The H6400 adds 3D playback and the new touch pad remote control. Voice recognition is an added plus thanks to the remote. You get is a 1080p display with a 120Hz refresh rate and a fully loaded Smart TV platform. These mid-tier models are designed to be feature packed but scale back on the picture quality features to keep the price down.\r \r Samsung UN65H6400, \r Samsung UN60H6400, \r Samsung UN55H6400, \r Samsung UN50H6400, \r Samsung UN48H6400\r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung H6350 Series LED TV  \r \r The H6350 series loses the 3D playback and extra control methods of the H6400 series. What you get is a 1080p display with a 120Hz refresh rate and a fully loaded quad core powered Smart TV platform. These models are designed for those who want decent picture quality and some extra options for the money.\r Samsung UN75H6350, \r Samsung UN65H6350, \r Samsung UN60H6350, \r Samsung UN55H6350, \r Samsung UN50H6350, \r Samsung UN48H6350, \r Samsung UN40H6350, \r Samsung UN32H6350, \r \r \r \r Samsung H6203 Series LED TV  \r \r The H6203 series sheds many picture quality features in order to be a value model LED TV for 2014. It''s 120Hz refresh rate and smart TV features really make this one shine, especially at the price point.\r Samsung UN65H6203, \r Samsung UN60H6203, \r Samsung UN55H6203, \r Samsung UN50H6203, \r Samsung UN46H6203, \r Samsung UN40H6203\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung H5500 Series LED TV  \r \r The H5500 series loses a lot of the features seen higher up in the line up. What''s left is a 1080p display with a 60Hz refresh rate. These models are perfect for those TV shopping on a budget or don''t need a smart TV platform to get more content on the screen.\r Samsung UN50H5500, \r Samsung UN48H5500, \r Samsung UN40H5500, \r Samsung UN32H5500\r \r \r \r \r Samsung EH5000 Series LED TV  \r The EH5000 series is Samsung''s lowest end line in the larger size LED backlit LCD TVs for 2012. It still has very nice appearance with a thin black bezel frame and 2" depth.\r \r Samsung UN50EH5000, \r Samsung UN46EH5000, \r Samsung UN40EH5000, \r Samsung UN32EH5000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung H4000 Series LED TV  \r \r The H4000 is as basic as it gets for Samsung LED TVs in 2014. These budget models feature 720p screens, 60Hz refresh rates, and only sport 1 HDMI port. These are perfect TVs for bedrooms, kid''s rooms, or the kitchen.\r Samsung UN28H4000\r \r \r \r \r 2013 and Early 2014 Samsug LCD & LED Televisions\r \r Samsung F9000 Series 4K LED TV  \r \r The F9000 series is Samsung''s attempt to break into the smaller sized 4K LED TVs for 2013/2014. It is loaded with features similar to the F8000 like voice interaction, Samsung''s Smart TV, a quad-core processor, and 2D to 3D conversion. Upgrades include the 4K screen and an improved on-board speaker system.\r Samsung UN55F9000, \r Samsung UN65F9000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung F8000 Series LED TV  \r \r The F8000 series is the top tier offering from Samsung for 2013/2014. It replaces the very popular ES8000. It is loaded with features ranging from voice interaction, Samsung''s Smart TV, a quad-core processor, and 2D to 3D conversion. \r Samsung UN75F8000, \r Samsung UN65F8000, \r Samsung UN60F8000, \r Samsung UN55F8000, \r Samsung UN46F8000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung F7500 Series LED TV  \r \r The F7500 series is a direct replacement of the ES7500 series. Many of the same features have rolled over, while the Smart Hub and design of the TV both got an overhaul. Smart Hub 2.0 recieved a speed upgrade in the form of a quad-core processor and a new navigation method the will be familiar to those who have used smartphones or tablets.\r Samsung UN60F7500, \r Samsung UN55F7500, \r Samsung UN46F7500\r \r \r \r \r Samsung F7100 Series LED TV  \r \r The F7100 series is a top candidate for a top quality value entry in 2013/2014. It is the 3rd teir from the top, meaning it is loaded with features for excellent picture quality. The Clear Coat screen, 240Hz processing, and micro dimming are all present. The quad-core processor and built-in front facing camera are missing. \r Samsung UN75F7100, \r Samsung UN65F7100, \r Samsung UN60F7100, \r Samsung UN55F7100, \r Samsung UN50F7100, \r Samsung UN46F7100\r \r \r \r \r Samsung F6800 Series LED TV  \r \r As the 4th tier model of Samsung''s 2013/2014 LED lineup, the F6800 series is quite surprising. The feature set is impressive with micro dimming, 3D, the "window design", and a native 240Hz panel. This one also goes with a dual core processor and an optional camera like the 7100 series above it.\r \r Samsung UN55F6800, \r Samsung UN50F6800, \r Samsung UN46F6800\r \r \r \r \r Samsung F6400 Series LED TV  \r \r The F6400 series in Samsung''s 2013/2014 lineup is quite the powerhouse when it comes to features. 3D playback and micro dimming are the heavy hitters. It shares features like Smart TV, a 120Hz panel, and the dual core processor of the F6300 models below it. These TVs have a great feature set with solid picture quality.\r Samsung UN75F6400, \r Samsung UN65F6400, \r Samsung UN60F6400, \r Samsung UN55F6400, \r Samsung UN50F6400, \r Samsung UN46F6400, \r Samsung UN40F6400\r \r \r \r \r Samsung F6300 Series LED TV  \r \r The F6300 series is identical to the F6400 seires above it minus the 3D functionality and micro dimming. It stands as a replacement for the popular ES6100 series from last year. Some of the features include Smart TV, a dual core processor, and a 120Hz panel.\r Samsung UN75F6300, \r Samsung UN65F6300, \r Samsung UN60F6300, \r Samsung UN55F6300, \r Samsung UN50F6300, \r Samsung UN46F6300, \r Samsung UN40F6300, \r Samsung UN32F6300\r \r \r \r \r Samsung FH6030 Series LED TV  \r \r The FH6030 series is a full array option in Samsung''s LED TV lineup for the year. It''s unique because it gets rid of all the internet connectivity but keep active 3D playback. This puts the FH6030 in a spot where there isn''t much competition. It is perfect for those looking for 3D and already have streaming media options.\r Samsung UN55FH6030, \r Samsung UN46FH6030, \r Samsung UN40FH6030\r \r \r \r \r Samsung FH6003 Series LED TV  \r \r The FH6003 series is another full array option in Samsung''s LED TV lineup for the year. This time things have been slimmed down even more. It is perfect for those looking for a new LED TV but aren''t interested in 3D or Smart TV features.\r Samsung UN60FH6003, \r Samsung UN55FH6003\r \r \r \r \r Samsung F5500 Series LED TV  \r \r The F5500 series is on the lower end of the LED/LCD spectrum for 2013/14, but it offers a solid value. The main difference from the F5000 series below it is the inclusion of Samsung''s Smart Hub. The 4 choices in size make it easy to find one for any room.\r Samsung UN50F5500, \r Samsung UN46F5500, \r Samsung UN40F5500, \r Samsung UN32F5500\r \r \r \r \r Samsung F5000 Series LED TV  \r \r The F5000 series is the lowest in the lineup with 1080p resolution. All picture quality, internet, and 3D features have been dropped to make this a budget model. The Full HD resolution is important because this TV is available in larger sizes.\r Samsung UN50F5000, \r Samsung UN46F5000, \r Samsung UN40F5000, \r Samsung UN32F5000, \r Samsung UN22F5000, \r \r \r \r \r Samsung FH5000 Series LED TV  \r \r The FH5000 series is identical to the F5000 models except for the type of backlighting. The FH5000 uses direct LED backlighting to create more uniform lighting on the screen. This in turn adds a little depth to the cabinet. This series is only available in the 39 inch size.\r Samsung UN39FH5000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung F4000 Series LED TV  \r \r The F4000 series is the last stop in the 2013/2014 Samsung LED TV lineup. It is a straight up budget model that offers 720p resolution with a 60Hz refresh rate. All the bells and whistles of 3D playback, internet connectivity, and picture quality features have been stripped. It is available in size 32 inch and smaller.\r Samsung UN32F4000, \r Samsung UN29F4000, \r Samsung UN19F4000\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r 2012 Samsug LCD & LED Televisions\r \r Samsung F9500 Series OLED TV  \r The Samsung F9500 OLED TV series is available for purchase by the end of 2012. This model is one of the first larger OLED TVs to be mass produced for the public, with its only competition this year coming from LG''s similar offering.\r \r Samsung KN55F9500 OLED TV\r \r \r Samsung ES8000 Series LED TV  \r New for the 2012 the ES8000 series LED television is the top of the line in LED back lit LCD televisions from Samsung. It looks fantastic with a slim .5" chrome bezel with picture going all the way to the edge. The black level and picture performance is impressive as are the expanded Smart TV features and the new Smart Interaction that lets you interat with your TV with hand motion and voice commands.\r \r Samsung UN75ES9000, Samsung UN65ES8000,\r Samsung UN60ES8000, \r \r Samsung UN55ES8000,\r Samsung UN46ES8000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung ES7500 Series LED TV  \r Samsung''s ES7500 series LED TVs also have the slim bezel like the ES8000 except it is charcoal instead of chrome. The ES7500 has most of the same picture features and the expanded Smart TV suite but it lacks the Smart Interaction. The panel is 480Hz 1080p with LED edge lighting.\r \r Samsung UN60ES7500, \r Samsung UN55ES7500, \r Samsung UN46ES7500\r \r \r \r \r Samsung ES7100 Series LED TV  \r Samsung''s ES7100 series replaces the D7000 line from 2011. This is the 3rd tier LED backlit LCD TV from Samsung for 2012. There are only two features it does not have from the higher tiered models – Smart Interaction through a built in camera, and Micro Dimming Ultimate.\r \r Samsung UN60ES7100, \r Samsung UN55ES7100, \r Samsung UN46ES7100\r \r \r \r \r Samsung ES6580 Series LED TV  \r The ES6580 is a mid level Samsung LED television though you wouldn''t really know it by the features. It has a 1080p, 480Hz LED back lit LCD panel and the Samsung Smart TV online suite. There are 1500 apps on the Samsung app store that range from streaming video to social media to games and many are available free of charge.\r \r \r Samsung UN55ES6580, \r Samsung UN46ES6580,\r Samsung UN40ES6580\r \r \r \r \r Samsung ES6500 Series LED TV  \r The ES6500 series is a mid-range edge lit LED backlit LCD TV from Samsung that combines a few of the best features from last years models from Samsung. It falls below the ES6800 and above the ES6100 in the lineup. It does not have 480Hz like the ES6800 but it does have the upgraded 240Hz processing frame rate speed.\r \r Samsung UN60ES6500, \r Samsung UN55ES6500, \r Samsung UN46ES6500\r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung ES6100 Series LED TV  \r The ES6100 series is a small step from the ES6500 series, these LED edge lit LCD televisions do contain the Samsung Smart TV online features but they are not 3D capable. This 1080p, 120Hz model is available in 4 sizes ranging from 60 inches to 40 inches.\r \r Samsung UN60ES6100, \r Samsung UN55ES6100, \r Samsung UN50ES6100, \r Samsung UN46ES6100\r \r \r \r \r Samsung EH6000 Series LED TV  \r The EH6000 series is a very slight step down from the ES6100 series in that it does not have the full Smart TV feature Apps available. It does have the premium Movie Apps capability and the same or similar picture quality updates such as the wide color enhancer. It is not a 3D capable TV, but it does give you 1080p, 120Hz processing and plenty of HDMI inputs. It is available in 5 sizes. Pricing should be competitive. Read our full review of these models here as follows:\r \r Samsung UN40EH6000, \r Samsung UN46EH6000, \r Samsung UN50EH6000, \r Samsung UN55EH6000,\r Samsung UN60EH6000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung EH5000 Series LED TV  \r The EH5000 series is Samsung''s lowest end line in the larger size LED backlit LCD TVs for 2012. It still has very nice appearance with a thin black bezel frame and 2" depth. It is only available in smaller sizes. 40" and 32", in 2012 the 5000 series gains the Smart TV feature.\r \r Samsung UN50EH5000, \r Samsung UN46EH5000, \r Samsung UN40EH5000, \r Samsung UN32EH5000\r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung EH4000 Series LED TV  \r The EH4000 series are line of small, value priced LED edge lit LCD televisions. With thin depths, sizes ranging from 32 inch to 19 inch and a PC input these models would not only make a good bedroom television, they also can double as a PC monitor.\r \r Samsung UN32EH4000, \r Samsung UN26EH4000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung EH5300 Series LED TV  \r The EH5300 series are line of lower end edge lit LED HDTVs from Samsung for 2012. The Smart TV Smart Hub feature is the highlight of this TV as described as follows, "Smart Hub: Samsung Smart TV has retooled its Smart Hub feature to further expand its access\r to a world of online entertainment.\r Samsung UN32EH5300,\r Samsung UN40EH5300,\r Samsung UN46EH5300,\r \r \r \r \r Samsung E550 Series LED TV  \r The E550 series is one of the only CCFL flourescent backlit LCD TVs Samsung will produce for 2012 and early 2013. It has full 1080p viewing and will be produced in 46”, as well as 40” and possibly 55” sizes. It is a straight forward value proposition no-frills sort of TV.\r Samsung LN46E550,\r Samsung LN40E550,\r \r \r 2011 / Early 2012 Samsung LED & LCD TV Models\r \r \r Samsung 8000 Series LED TV  \r \r See Review\r Samsung''s D8000 3D LED/LCD TV relaces the C8000 series in 2011, they have a new, more modern look with a picture that extends nearly all the way to the edge and an expanded internet TV line up that features a full web browser.\r \r Samsung UN65D8000, \r Samsung UN55D8000, \r Samsung UN46D8000\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung 7000 Series LED TV  \r \r See Review\r The D7000 replaces the C7000, one level below the 8000 series it contains most of the same features but drops the full web browser and has a slightly different look and is available as a 60" model instead of a 65"\r \r Samsung UN60D7000, \r Samsung UN55D7000, \r Samsung UN46D7000\r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung 6400 Series LED TV  \r \r The D6400 series from Samsung is an LCD panel with LED backlighting and full 3D. It has a solid value offering and is available in one of the largest varieties of sizes 40", 46", 55" and 60". \r \r Samsung UN60D6400, \r Samsung UN55D6400, \r Samsung UN46D6400, \r Samsung UN40D6400\r \r \r \r \r Samsung 6300 Series LED TV  \r \r See Review\r The D6300 series has all the featurs of the D6000 series but all Samsung''s new Allshare feature for streaming media over your home network and compaible devices. This competitively priced LED backlit LCD provides good value.\r \r \r Samsung UN55D6300, \r Samsung UN46D6300, \r Samsung UN40D6300\r \r \r \r \r Samsung 6000 Series LED TV  \r \r See Review\r The D6000 line of 1080p LED TVs is another line of competitively priced LED TVs available in larger sizes. The 6000 line is considered an entry level LED television and provides good bang for the buck in the LED market.\r \r \r Samsung UN55D6000, \r Samsung UN46D6000, \r Samsung UN40D6000, \r Samsung UN32D6000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung 5500 Series LED TV  \r \r See Review\r The D5500 line of LED TVs represents a smaller sized, lower priced option perfect for bedrooms or dorm rooms. It may not have all the features of the higher end models but if you want a slim line LED/LCD at a good price the D5500 is worth a look.\r \r Samsung UN40D5500, \r Samsung UN32D5500\r \r \r \r \r Samsung 4003 Series LED TV  \r \r The 4003 line of small LED TVs is aimed at bringing LED back lighting to sizes normally reserved for LCD and at a lower price point. The 720p, 60Hz panel isn''t going to blow you away but these models do have good looks and picture quality at their price point.\r \r Samsung UN32D4003, \r Samsung UN26D4003\r \r \r \r \r Samsung 2011 Series 6 LCD  \r The 2011 D630 series are CCFL backlit LCD TVs that include Samsung''s new Allshare feature that allows you to stream media from your home network to the TV, it also features built-in WiFi for easy access to your home network. We were highly impressed with the 6 series ast year and expect this year to be the same.\r \r Samsung LN46D630, \r Samsung LN40D630\r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung 2011 Series 5 LCD  \r For 2011 the D550 series of CCFL backlit LCDs replaces the C550. These LCDs offer quality at an affordable price. Last year''s 5 series televisions were a good bargin and there is no reason why they shouldn''t remain so in 2011.\r \r Samsung LN46D550, \r Samsung LN40D550, \r Samsung LN37D550, \r Samsung LN32D550\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung 2011 Series 4 LCD  \r \r See Review\r The 720p, 60Hz D450 line replaces the C450 line from 2010. These small, affordable LCD TVs make for an excellent TV in the bedroom, office or kitchen. See our review for a full breakdown of the D450''s performance and features.\r \r Samsung LN19D450,\r Samsung LN22D450, \r Samsung LN26D450, \r Samsung LN32D403, \r Samsung LN32D405, \r Samsung LN32D450\r \r \r \r \r 2010 Samsung LCD & LED Televisions\r \r Samsung 9000 Series LED TV  \r See Review\r Samsung''s flagship line at CES 2010 is the 9 series of LED televisions. Home entertainment innovation abounds in these TVs from the pedestal stand/wall mount bracket containing all the cirsuitry to the touch screen remote control than display broadcast signals on the screen. Throw in the .28 inch depth of the unit and the built in internet connectivity and you have a serious home entertinment hub for your TV room.\r \r Samsung UN55C9000, \r Samsung UN46C9000\r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung 8000 Series LED TV  \r Samsung''s 8000 series LED TVs for 2010 feature 3D capability in a slim, contemporary design thanks to the LED edge lighting. Samsung''s proprietary 3D system allows compatibility with multiple 3D formats to provide access to 3D content from many sources.\r \r Samsung UN65C8000, \r Samsung UN60C8000, \r Samsung UN55C8000, \r Samsung UN46C8000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung 7000 Series LED TV  \r See Review\r Samsung''s 7000 series LED TVs for 2010 feature a new contemporary design thanks to the LED edge lighting. In fact the depth of the unit looked to us to be around the same 1.2 inches in depth from the 2009 model. The big difference that we noticed at CES 2010 in aesthetics was the much smaller bezel/frame which was only about 1 inch on top and sides of the TV screen.\r \r Samsung UN55C7000, \r Samsung UN46C7000, \r Samsung UN40C7000\r \r \r \r \r Samsung 6500 Series LED TV  \r See Review\r Samsung''s 6500 series LED TVs for 2010 feature a new contemporary design thanks to the LED edge lighting. The C6500 series LEDs wil have the AutoMotion 120Hz refresh rate, and a 1080p "Ultra Clear" panel. The 6300 line has all the features of the 6500 without the internet connectivity. \r \r Samsung UN65C6500, \r Samsung UN60C6500, \r Samsung UN55C6500, \r Samsung UN55C6300, \r Samsung UN46C6500, \r Samsung UN46C6300, \r Samsung UN40C6500, \r Samsung UN40C6300\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung Series 7 LCD  \r See Review\r The LNB750 Series is a CFL backlit series of 1080p, 240Hz LCDs with built in ehternet access to Samsung''s Internet@TV.\r \r \r Samsung LN46C750\r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung Series 6 LCD  \r See Review\r Samsung announced another CFL backlit line of LCD televisions at CES 2010, the C650 series of LCDs feature Samsung''s 1080p, 120Hz "Ultra Clear" panel. The popular red Touch of Color bezel returns for 2010 on the C650 line and while the C650 doesn''t share the sleek, metallic designs of the LED line up it''s still a good looking television. The C630 line carry all the features of the C650 but lack the internet connectivity.\r \r Samsung LN55C650, \r Samsung LN55C630, \r Samsung LN46C650, \r Samsung LN46C630, \r Samsung LN40C650, \r Samsung LN40C630, \r Samsung LN37C650, \r Samsung LN32C650\r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung Series 4 LCD  \r See Review\r Samsung''s 2010 4 Series LCDs are a step up from the 3 series. Available in the same sizes they still feature a 60Hz, 720p, CFL backlit panel, with SRS TruSurround HD. They add a third HDMI input, the ability to watch video off a USB thumb drive and Samsung''s AnyNet+ which allows communication between similarly equipped Samsung home theater equipment.\r \r Samsung LN19C450,\r Samsung LN22C450, \r Samsung LN26C450, \r Samsung LN32C450\r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung Series 3 LCD  \r See Review\r The 2010 3 Series LCDs feature flourescent backlighting, 720p panels, 2 HDMI inputs and SRS TruSurround HD audio processing. They are affordable sets that make an excellent choice for smaller rooms in your house or in a boat or recreational vehicle.\r \r Samsung LN19C350,\r Samsung LN22C350, \r Samsung LN26C350, \r Samsung LN32C350\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung Official Site\r Samsung TV Picture Settings\r Samsung Service\r Compare TV Ratings\r LCD TV Reviews\r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung LCD and LED 2012 TV Models\r \r \r Samsung UN55E9000, \r Samsung UN65ES8000, \r Samsung UN55ES8000, \r Samsung UN46ES8000, \r Samsung UN55ES7500, \r Samsung UN55E7000, \r Samsung UN46E7400, \r Samsung UN46E7000, \r Samsung UN40E7000, \r Samsung UN46ES6800, \r Samsung UN55E6400, \r Samsung UN55E6000, \r Samsung UN46E6000, \r Samsung UN32E4000, \r Samsung LN40E550, \r Samsung LN32E450\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r   \r \r \r \r \r \r \r LCD/LED TV Manufacturers\r Sony LCD/LED TV\r Samsung LCD/LED TV\r Sharp LCD/LED TV \r Panasonic LCD/LED TV \r LG LCD/LED TV\r Toshiba LCD/LED TV\r Vizio LCD/LED TV \r JVC LCD/LED TV\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r     \r \r  TOP 10 Best Selling LCD/LED TVS\r \r \r  1\r   Samsung UN55H7150 \r \r \r  2\r   LG 55LB7200 \r \r \r  3\r   Sony KDL-50W800B \r \r \r  4\r   LG 42LB5800 \r \r \r  5\r   Vizio E550i-B1 \r \r \r  6\r   Sony KDL-48W600B \r \r \r  7\r   Samsung UN50HU8550 \r \r \r  8\r   Samsung UN48H6350 \r \r \r  9\r   Vizio M552i-B2 \r \r \r  10\r   Vizio E320i-B2 \r \r \r  \r \r \r Last Update:\r April 2015 \r  \r \r \r \r    \r   \r \r  Recommended TVs By Size\r \r \r \r 19" LCD TV\r 42" LCD/LED TV\r \r \r 20" LCD TV\r 46" LCD/LED TV\r \r \r 26" LCD TV\r 55" LCD/LED TV\r \r \r 32" LCD/LED TV\r 60"+ LCD/LED TV\r \r \r 37" LCD/LED TV\r 70"+ LCD/LED TV\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r    \r   \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung UN50H6400\r New! 2014 50" Smart LED TV $1197 from our dealers Shop\r \r \r \r \r \r LG 42LB5800\r 2014 42" LED Smart TV Now $479! from Amazon Shop\r \r \r \r \r \r Samsung 32EH5000\r 32" Budget LED TV Now $247! from Amazon Shop\r \r \r \r \r \r Sharp LC-70EQ10U\r New 2014 70" Smart LED TV Now $1987 from Amazon Shop\r \r \r \r \r Vizio E550i-B2\r 55" 2014 LED Smart TV $698! from Amazon Shop\