(177, 'Android Sync\r   Google Sync\r   iPhone/iPad Sync\r   Windows Phone Sync\r   BlackBerry Sync\r   Support\r   Downloads\r    Free 14-day trialSoftware Updates\r   Buy Now\r    \r     \r     \r     \r     \r    \r   \r  \r  \r  \r \r  \r \r  Sync Samsung Galaxy S5 with standalone Microsoft Outlook. No Exchange required.\r \r  #1 selling Android sync software. Sync Outlook contacts, calendar, tasks, notes, and categories with the Samsung Galaxy S5 other Galaxy devices: Samsung Galaxy S4 (S IV) Samsung Galaxy SIII (S3), Galaxy Nexus, Galaxy SII (S2), Galaxy Note 3, Galaxy Victory, Galaxy S Relay 4G, Galaxy SII Epic 4G Touch, Samsung Galaxy Prevail, Samsung Fascinate, \r  Samsung Vibrant, Samsung Captivate, Samsung Epic 4G, Samsung Continuum, \r  Samsung Galaxy i9000, Samsung Showcase, and Samsung Mesmerize.\r \r Prices start at $14.95. Click here for more info.\r Our software is unique because it handles advanced Outlook fields including category colors, File-As settings, full contact notes, tasks, journal, and contact photos, etc. You can choose how to sync: USB, WiFi, Cloud, or using your Gmail account. \r \r \r About the Samsung Galaxy S5\r   \r   Samsung Galaxy S5 is Samsung''s flagship device for 2014. It ships with Android KitKat (4.4.2), 5.1-inch HD display with an amazing 432ppi of rich color and visual density. A built-in heart rate sensor and the accompanying S Health app help manage your personal life. A new fingerprint scanner lets you protect your device to unique fingerprint. The Galaxy S5 is water resistant with an IP67 certification, allowing you to drop GS5 in up to 3 feet of without damage.\r   \r    Android 4.4.2 "KitKat"\r    Qualcomm Snapdragon 801 chipset\r    2GB RAM, 16GB built-in storage5.1" FHD Super AMOLED (1920 x 1080), 432 ppi\r    142.0 x 72.5 x 8.1mm, 145g\r    16 megapixel camera with LED flash\r    LTE Cat.4 (150/50Mbps)\r   \r \r \r   About the Samsung Galaxy S III\r   \r   Samsung Galaxy S III is Samsung''s flagship device for 2012. As expected, it contains top-of-the-line hardware, including a 4.8" HD Super AMOLED display. Samsung has also added some new software features. The Galaxy S3 will use the front facing camera to detect your eyes and keep the display on while youre looking at it. It also features a smart voice assistant, similar to Apple''s Siri. All this runs on the newest Android 4.0 platform.\r   \r    Android 4.0 "Ice Cream Sandwich"\r    1.5 GHz Dual-core CPU (Quad core internationally)\r    4.8" Super AMOLED HD display (1280x720)\r    8 megapixel camera with LED flash\r    4G HSDPA+/LTE (regional availablity), Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r    \r  \r \r \r  \r   About the Samsung Galaxy Note II\r   \r   Nobody expected the original Galaxy Note to sell as well as it did - it was a surprise hit. Samsung took this as a sign to go even bigger. The new Galaxy Note II (Galaxy Note 2) upps the screen size to 5.5 inches, and borrows the body styling from their flagship Galaxy S III.\r   \r    Android 4.1 "Jelly Bean"\r    1.6 GHz Quad-core CPU\r    Up to 64GB internal storage\r    5.5" Super AMOLED display\r    8 megapixel camera with full HD (1920x1080) 1080p video recording. \r    LTE, Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r    \r  \r \r  \r  \r   About the Galaxy Nexus\r   \r   The Galaxy Nexus by Samsung is the first Android 4.0 "Ice Cream Sandwich" device from Google. Featuring the very latest in technology, the Galaxy Nexus sets the bar for other devices to follow. Highlights include the supple 4.65" screen running at full 1280x720 HD resolution, curved display and form factor, and an NFC chip for touch-and-go payments.\r   \r    Android 4.0 "Ice Cream Sandwich"\r    1.2 GHz Dual-core CPU\r    4.65" Super AMOLED HD display (1280x720)\r    5 megapixel camera with zero shutter lag\r    4G HSDPA+/LTE, Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r    \r  \r  \r  \r  \r   About the Galaxy S Relay 4G\r   \r   The Galaxy S Relay 4G packs the latest hardware into a smaller (by today''s standards) 4" display and adds a QWERTY keyboard. Affordably priced, the Galaxy S Relay 4G will run on T-Mobile''s high-speed HSPA+ network. \r   \r    Android 4.0 "Ice Cream Sandwich"\r    1.5 GHz Dual-core CPU\r    4.0" display\r    5 megapixel camera\r    4G HSDPA+, Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r    \r  \r  \r  \r  \r   About the Galaxy Victory\r   \r   The Galaxy Victory is an affordable Android phone from Samsung. While the Victory doesn''t have the most top-of-the-line specs, it makes up for it with a small package and affordable price.\r   \r    Android 4.0 "Ice Cream Sandwich"\r    1.2 GHz Dual-core CPU\r    4.0" display\r    5 megapixel camera\r    4G LTE, Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r    \r  \r  \r  \r  \r   About the Samsung Galaxy S II\r   \r   Samsung Galaxy S II (including the Epic 4G Touch from Sprint and the Skyrocket 4G from AT&T) is the sequel to the critically-acclaimed Samsung Galaxy S Android smartphone. \r   It comes with the newer Android 2.3 Gingerbread OS, and an even larger screen at 4.3 inches of Super \r   AMOLED Plus goodness. The Galaxy S II upgrades the camera to 8MP and adds an LED flash to it, together \r   with 1080p video recording. A 1GHz dual-core chipset is running the show so as to deliver a fine \r   performance without any hints of lag.\r   \r    Android 2.3 "Gingerbread"\r    1GHz Dual core Hummingbird CPU\r    32GB built-in flash memory. MicroSD card will give additional 32GB, total = 64GB\r    4.3" Super AMOLED 2 display\r    8 megapixel camera with full HD (1920x1080) 1080p video recording. \r    Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r    \r  \r  \r  \r  \r   About the Samsung Galaxy Note 10.1\r   \r   Samsung made waves with the first Galaxy Note, a hybrid tablet/phone. Now, they are extending the Note line into a full tablet format. Like the original, the Galaxy Note 10.1 contains a special stylus pen that can be used with certain applications. \r   \r    Android 4.0 "Ice Cream Sandwich"\r    1.4 GHz Quad-core CPU\r    2GB RAM, 16GB storage\r    10.1" display (1280x800)\r    5 megapixel camera with LED flash\r    Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r    \r  \r  \r \r  \r   About the Samsung Galaxy Note\r   \r   Big is back. Featuring a massive 5.3-inch screen with a resolution of 800x1280, the Samsung Galaxy Note is one of the largest phones available. It doesn''t hurt that Samsung loaded this beast up with a dual-core processor and 1GB of RAM, making this one of the largest and most powerful devices this 2011 holiday season. The Galaxy Note is truly without peer.\r   \r    Android 2.3 "Gingerbread"\r    1.4 GHz Dual-core CPU\r    16/32GB built-in flash memory. MicroSD card will give additional 32GB\r    5.3" Super AMOLED display\r    8 megapixel camera with full HD (1920x1080) 1080p video recording. \r    Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r    \r  \r  \r  \r  \r   About the Samsung Galaxy Prevail\r   \r   Galaxy Prevail is an Android smartphone with 3.2" display. It has 2MP camera, GPS, Bluetooth, E-mail access \r   and supports up to 32GB microSD memory cards.\r   \r    Android 2.2 "Froyo"\r    800MHz CPU\r    32GB built-in flash memory. MicroSD card will give additional 32GB, total = 64GB\r    3.2-inch touchscreen\r    2 megapixel camera with video recording.\r    Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r   \r  \r \r  \r  \r   About the Samsung Fascinate\r   \r   The Samsung Fascinate is Verizon''s first Galaxy S smartphone device. The Fascinate offers an AMOLED touchscreen with virtual QWERTY keyboard, multi-touch pinch to zoom, and horizontal swiping. Other key features include a 1GHz Cortex A8 Hummingbird Application Processor, Swype text technology, and a 5MP camera with video capture, and LED flash.\r   \r    Android 2.1\r    1GHz Cortex A8 Hummingbird Processor\r    512MB RAM\r    4-inch Capacitive Touch Screen running at 480 x 800 resolution\r    5MP Auto focus, Smile detection, Digital zoom, Multi shot, Effects, Self-timer, Panorama, ISO control\r    Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r   \r  \r \r \r  \r   About the Samsung Vibrant\r   \r   Samsung Vibrant utilizes a large 4-inch WVGA, Super AMOLED screen, a 1GHz processor and the Android 2.1 operating system. The camera is 5MP with the ability to record 720p HD video at 30 frames per second. Other goodies include 3G, Wi-Fi and A-GPS\r   \r    Android 2.1\r    1GHz Cortex A8 Hummingbird Processor\r    16GB storage, 512 MB RAM\r    4-inch Capacitive Touch Screen running at 480 x 800 resolution\r    5MP 2592 x 1944 pixels, autofocus\r    Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r   \r  \r \r \r  \r   About the Samsung Captivate\r   \r   Samsung Captivate I897 is AT&T''s version of the Samsung GALAXY S, and while it''s pretty identical in terms of features, its design has undergone some visible changes. Nonetheless, it still has the GALAXY S branding on its back. The Samsung Captivate is a high-end Android smartphone with its 4-inch Super AMOLED screen, 5MP camera with HD video recording and 1GHz Hummingbird processor.\r   \r    Android 2.1\r    1GHz Cortex A8 Hummingbird Processor\r    16GB ROM/512MB RAM - expanable to 32GB\r    4-inch Super AMOLED Touch Screen running at 480 x 800 resolution\r    5MP 2592 x 1944 pixels, autofocus, Smile detection, Digital zoom, Multi shot, Effects, Self-timer, Panorama, ISO control\r    Video Capture - 1280x720 (720p HD) (29 fps)\r    Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r   \r  \r  \r \r  \r   About the Samsung Epic 4G\r   \r   Samsung Epic 4G is an Android 2.1 powered device heading for Sprint. It sports a full QWERTY keyboard, 4-inch Super AMOLED display, powerful 1GHz processor, 512MB of RAM, WiMAX connectivity and many more.\r   \r    Android 2.1\r    1GHz Cortex A8 Hummingbird Processor\r    1GB of ROM, 512 MB of RAM - expanable to 32GB\r    4-inch Super AMOLED Touch Screen running at 480 x 800 resolution\r    5MP camera with 3x digital zoom, LED flash\r    720p video recording, front-facing VGA camera\r    Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r   \r  \r \r \r  \r   About the Samsung Continuum\r   \r   Samsung Epic 4G is an Android 2.1 powered device heading for Sprint. It sports a full QWERTY keyboard, 4-inch Super AMOLED display, powerful 1GHz processor, 512MB of RAM, WiMAX connectivity and many more.\r   \r    Android 2.1\r    1GHz Cortex A8 Hummingbird Processor\r    1GB of ROM, 512 MB of RAM - expanable to 32GB\r    4-inch Super AMOLED Touch Screen running at 480 x 800 resolution\r    5MP camera with 3x digital zoom, LED flash\r    720p video recording, front-facing VGA camera\r    Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and GPS connectivity\r   \r  \r  \r \r \r \r \r \r  \r   \r   © Copyright 1996-2015 by CompanionLink Software, Inc. 811 SW Naito Parkway Suite 600, Portland, OR 97204\r  \r  \r  \r   Proudly in business since 1988.\r   \r   \r    \r    \r    \r    \r   \r   \r   Contact Us / OEM Cloud Sync / About Us / Blog / Terms / Privacy / Press');
